.TH CMT_PREFETCH 3 "LIBCMT" "CMT_PREFETCH" "Prefetch Memory Functions"

.SH NAME
CMT_PREFETCH \- Reduce cache-miss latency by preloading memory into CPU cache

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #define INCL__PREFETCH
.br
.B #include <LIBCMT/LIBCMT.h>

.SH FILES
LIBCMT/FUNCTIONS/PREFETCH.h

.SH DESCRIPTION
Macros and functions to hint the CPU to preload memory into its cache for faster access.

.TP
.B PREFETCH, prefetch()
Load a specific memory value into the CPU cache before use.

.TP
.B PREFETCHW, prefetchw()
Same as PREFETCH, but indicates the data may be modified.

.TP
.B SPIN_LOCK_PREFETCH, spin_lock_prefetch()
Prefetch spin locks (UNIX only).

.TP
.B PREFETCH_RANGE, prefetch_range()
Prefetch a block or range of memory.

.SH USAGE
Prefetch a single value:
.nf
int variable[9471];
int number = 42;

PREFETCH(variable[0]);
// or
prefetch(number);
.fi

Prefetch a memory block or array:
.nf
PREFETCH_RANGE(variable, sizeof(variable));
// or
prefetch_range(variable, 100);
.fi

.SH NOTES
- PREFETCH only hints the CPU; it does not guarantee data placement in cache.
- Use PREFETCH_RANGE for large arrays or buffers to minimize cache misses.

